{
  "texts": [
    "There is also the issue of model extraction attacks, where the aim is to steal the original models by training surrogate models (Lee et al. 2022).",
    "However, recent studies have detected these issues, and already formulated solutions to tackle these issues, such as Guo et al. (2022), Lee et al. (2022), and Rawat et al. (2022).",
    "In terms of future risks of AI, Radanliev et al. (2022a) forecasts that an increase of investment on edge computing will lead to more autonomous machines.",
    "This is in line with one of our future research directions, of AutoML developing to include unsupervised tasks.",
    "This increasing automation and \"self-reliance\" of ML algorithms may lead to bias, as setting the wrong direction at the start of a self-evolving, self-procreating AI may escalate into bigger risks and possible damages."
  ]
}